    <string name="tooltip_ras">Your 7-day rolling Readylytics Activity Score (RAS).\nBased on how often and how
        hard you challenge your heart.\n\n• 100+: Optimal\n• 75-99: Neutral\n• 50-74: Warning\n•
        &lt; 50: Poor</string>
    <string name="tooltip_readiness">Preparation for stress based on recent load &amp;
        recovery.\n\n• 85–100: Peak\n• 60–84: Maintain\n• 30–59: Caution\n• &lt; 30: High Fatigue</string>
    <string name="tooltip_strain_ratio">The ACWR (Acute:Chronic Workload Ratio). Compares recent
        training load to your baseline.\n\n• 0.8–1.3: In your normal range — sweet spot\n• 1.3–1.5:
        Load increasing; linear decay begins\n• 1.5–2.0: Overtraining; high injury risk\n• &gt;2.0:
        Severe overtraining; recovery needed\n• 0.5–0.8: Under-training\n• &lt;0.5: Severe
        under-training</string>
